1
00:00:19,467 --> 00:00:22,300
You've really changed a lot,
Celeste.

2
00:00:22,367 --> 00:00:26,333
Maybe anyone who had a bad past
would not look back.

3
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:28,533
I was really traumatized.

4
00:00:28,600 --> 00:00:31,500
Father hurt me and up to now,
he's still hurting me.

5
00:00:31,567 --> 00:00:33,733
Do I need to kiss her feet

6
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:36,033
so she could forgive me?

7
00:00:36,133 --> 00:00:39,700
Be more understanding
with my daughter.

8
00:00:39,767 --> 00:00:42,867
Yes, Patricio,
I'll do that for you.

9
00:00:42,933 --> 00:00:44,667
But I'm just human...

10
00:00:44,733 --> 00:00:48,900
I don't know how long
I can endure your daughter.

11
00:00:48,967 --> 00:00:50,867
I was also hurt before.

12
00:00:50,933 --> 00:00:52,167
We're the same.

13
00:00:52,233 --> 00:00:53,567
The difference between us is,

14
00:00:53,633 --> 00:00:55,867
I'm willing to give a second
chance to the person

15
00:00:55,933 --> 00:00:58,400
who has hurt me.

16
00:00:58,467 --> 00:01:00,267
A second chance
to make up for it.

17
00:01:00,333 --> 00:01:01,500
You should too.

18
00:01:01,567 --> 00:01:03,133
Nothing is perfect.

19
00:01:03,200 --> 00:01:04,700
Everyone makes a mistake.

20
00:01:04,767 --> 00:01:06,267
Tonito, don't you find this
exciting?

21
00:01:06,333 --> 00:01:07,800
Celeste doesn't have to know.

22
00:01:07,900 --> 00:01:09,500
Please stop this foolishness.

23
00:01:09,567 --> 00:01:10,967
Can't you understand
that we're done?

24
00:01:11,033 --> 00:01:13,633
Maybe it's meant to happen

25
00:01:13,700 --> 00:01:15,800
because I just got carried away.

26
00:01:15,867 --> 00:01:17,067
This is not right.

27
00:01:17,133 --> 00:01:18,933
Celeste is the woman
that I love now...

28
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:21,333
and I will never cheat on her.

29
00:01:21,400 --> 00:01:22,967
I want to go home.

30
00:01:23,033 --> 00:01:26,500
I'm sure Tonito
is already worried about me.

31
00:01:28,300 --> 00:01:29,467
Annoying...

32
00:01:29,533 --> 00:01:35,033
Of all the people here,
Mikoy is the one I'm with.

33
00:01:36,767 --> 00:01:38,700
Well, if you think about it...

34
00:01:38,767 --> 00:01:41,533
if Ms.Vangie is with me here...

35
00:01:41,633 --> 00:01:43,000
I would only be annoyed.

36
00:02:24,900 --> 00:02:26,833
Do you still remember this tree?

37
00:02:28,667 --> 00:02:31,167
No, I just passed by it.

38
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:34,467
Impossible.

39
00:02:34,533 --> 00:02:38,500
Do you remember the day I carved
this...

40
00:02:38,567 --> 00:02:42,900
was also the day...

41
00:02:42,967 --> 00:02:44,833
we kissed?

42
00:02:44,900 --> 00:02:46,300
Hey!

43
00:02:46,367 --> 00:02:48,233
Are you hallucinating?

44
00:02:48,333 --> 00:02:49,733
No kiss took place.

45
00:03:04,600 --> 00:03:05,733
There, it's done!

46
00:03:06,833 --> 00:03:09,900
Why do you have to carve that?

47
00:03:09,967 --> 00:03:12,567
Because this will remind you
how much I love you.

48
00:03:14,433 --> 00:03:16,467
Maybe you're just saying
that now.

49
00:03:16,533 --> 00:03:17,967
Of course not.

50
00:03:18,033 --> 00:03:21,667
As long our names are carved
on this tree,

51
00:03:21,767 --> 00:03:23,167
my love for you
will not be gone, Celeste.

52
00:03:25,100 --> 00:03:28,600
Here...

53
00:03:28,667 --> 00:03:29,967
I got these from the farm.

54
00:03:30,033 --> 00:03:31,467
I picked them for you.

55
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:33,767
This is beautiful.

56
00:03:33,833 --> 00:03:36,033
You are more beautiful
than that, Celeste.

57
00:03:36,100 --> 00:03:37,700
Do you know the myth
about Mirasol (Sunflower)?

58
00:03:38,767 --> 00:03:39,967
No. What?

59
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:43,667
That's called Mirasol
or Sunflower.

60
00:03:43,733 --> 00:03:46,533
There are two lovers,
a man, and a woman.

61
00:03:46,600 --> 00:03:50,300
They got separated
but the man didn't give up.

62
00:03:51,233 --> 00:03:54,067
He waited until death
for the woman's return.

63
00:03:55,033 --> 00:03:58,000
In his grave,
a Sunflower bloomed.

64
00:03:59,367 --> 00:04:01,133
The man loved her so much.

65
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:04,200
He really waited until death?

66
00:04:04,833 --> 00:04:11,567
Yes, and in case,
we get separated,

67
00:04:11,633 --> 00:04:13,133
I will still wait for you.

68
00:04:13,200 --> 00:04:15,633
I will still wait for you
to come back, Celeste,

69
00:04:15,700 --> 00:04:16,867
because I love you so much.

70
00:04:19,467 --> 00:04:21,567
You will also wait
for me until death?

71
00:04:22,200 --> 00:04:23,633
Yes, until death.

72
00:04:55,067 --> 00:04:56,967
What?

73
00:04:57,033 --> 00:04:58,100
Have you forgotten?

74
00:04:59,433 --> 00:05:01,267
As far as I remember,

75
00:05:01,367 --> 00:05:05,667
after you carved
that you wanted to kiss me.

76
00:05:05,733 --> 00:05:06,667
But I didn't want to.

77
00:05:06,733 --> 00:05:08,233
I didn't allow you.

78
00:05:08,300 --> 00:05:09,300
You're terrible,

79
00:05:09,367 --> 00:05:11,800
we just became ex-lovers
and you edit the truth.

80
00:05:11,867 --> 00:05:13,267
What do you mean
I edited it?

81
00:05:14,467 --> 00:05:15,533
Here's what happened.

82
00:05:17,300 --> 00:05:18,467
You will also wait
for me...

83
00:05:19,900 --> 00:05:21,800
until death? Really?

84
00:05:21,867 --> 00:05:23,133
Until death...

85
00:05:29,733 --> 00:05:31,200
Hey...

86
00:05:31,267 --> 00:05:32,467
Hey, Celeste!

87
00:05:34,367 --> 00:05:35,967
Why did you run away from me?

88
00:05:36,833 --> 00:05:38,433
I said I love you so much.

89
00:05:39,133 --> 00:05:40,167
Don't you have anything to say?

90
00:05:40,233 --> 00:05:42,133
Will you not say yes to me?

91
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:43,600
You don't love me?

92
00:05:49,700 --> 00:05:51,200
I love you so much, Celeste!

93
00:05:51,267 --> 00:05:52,867
I love you!

94
00:05:55,367 --> 00:05:56,933
I love you, Celeste!

95
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:58,267
I love you so much!

96
00:06:00,800 --> 00:06:02,667
I love you, Celeste!

97
00:06:10,400 --> 00:06:11,533
You're so great, Mikoy!

98
00:06:13,400 --> 00:06:14,600
What? Do you remember now?

99
00:06:17,233 --> 00:06:18,333
I'm right?

100
00:06:18,400 --> 00:06:21,700
I'm correct, right?

101
00:06:21,767 --> 00:06:23,333
Say it. Yes?

102
00:06:24,367 --> 00:06:25,333
Who kissed?

103
00:06:26,700 --> 00:06:27,767
Who?

104
00:06:30,133 --> 00:06:30,933
Who?

105
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:33,133
- Me.
- Oh...

106
00:06:33,200 --> 00:06:34,233
On the cheek.

107
00:06:36,767 --> 00:06:38,233
You edited it again.

108
00:06:38,300 --> 00:06:39,367
No, that's right.

109
00:06:40,300 --> 00:06:41,400
You're right.

110
00:06:43,400 --> 00:06:46,100
Do you remember the first kiss
on the lips?

111
00:06:50,067 --> 00:06:51,333
- No.
 - No?

112
00:07:03,500 --> 00:07:05,800
Did you contact Mikoy?

113
00:07:05,867 --> 00:07:07,433
No, not yet.

114
00:07:07,500 --> 00:07:09,100
I don't know if his battery
is drained

115
00:07:09,167 --> 00:07:10,367
or if he has a signal
or he doesn't!

116
00:07:11,533 --> 00:07:13,200
His battery is probably drained,
Father.

117
00:07:13,267 --> 00:07:15,000
They've been there
since yesterday!

118
00:07:15,100 --> 00:07:18,100
Maybe Mikoy hasn't been able
to charge his phone yet.

119
00:07:18,167 --> 00:07:21,633
Why is he and Celeste
not here yet?

120
00:07:21,700 --> 00:07:23,500
That's what I'm thinking.

121
00:07:23,567 --> 00:07:26,100
I don't know what happened
to them!

122
00:07:26,167 --> 00:07:28,267
Father, don't be stressed.

123
00:07:28,333 --> 00:07:29,667
Just relax.

124
00:07:29,733 --> 00:07:32,167
We know Mikoy.

125
00:07:32,233 --> 00:07:35,000
And when he said he will bring
Celeste home,

126
00:07:35,067 --> 00:07:36,267
I'm sure of that.

127
00:07:37,200 --> 00:07:38,933
That's right.

128
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:41,967
Mikoy will take care of Celeste,
okay?

129
00:07:42,033 --> 00:07:46,233
Maybe he's happy
because they are together.

130
00:07:46,300 --> 00:07:48,167
Mother is nosy.

131
00:07:48,267 --> 00:07:50,233
How do you know?

132
00:07:50,300 --> 00:07:51,800
Who knows?

133
00:07:51,867 --> 00:07:53,667
You still don't know those
things.

134
00:07:53,733 --> 00:07:55,167
Just deliver these pili.

135
00:07:55,233 --> 00:07:55,933
I already know that.

136
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:57,567
Oh...

137
00:07:57,633 --> 00:07:58,633
By the way, Mother,

138
00:07:58,700 --> 00:08:00,367
when I'm already done
with the delivery,

139
00:08:00,433 --> 00:08:04,533
I will help some people
from Manila with their projects.

140
00:08:04,600 --> 00:08:05,800
Who are they?

141
00:08:05,867 --> 00:08:07,733
They are just students, Mother.

142
00:08:07,800 --> 00:08:09,600
I mentioned them to you before.

143
00:08:09,667 --> 00:08:11,067
Okay, take care.

144
00:08:11,933 --> 00:08:13,933
Sebastian, you take care, okay?

145
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:16,067
Don't forget to call.

146
00:08:16,133 --> 00:08:17,833
Yes, Father.

147
00:08:17,900 --> 00:08:19,067
Bye.

148
00:08:19,133 --> 00:08:19,933
Okay.

149
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:28,900
And who is this?

150
00:08:30,033 --> 00:08:31,233
Hello?

151
00:08:31,300 --> 00:08:32,833
Hello, Sir?

152
00:08:32,900 --> 00:08:35,133
This is Tonito.

153
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:36,033
Do you remember me?

154
00:08:36,100 --> 00:08:37,467
I'm Celeste's fiancé.

155
00:08:38,233 --> 00:08:39,967
Yes, Tonito.

156
00:08:40,033 --> 00:08:42,400
I just want to know
how Celeste is.

157
00:08:42,467 --> 00:08:44,733
I can't get through her
phone since yesterday.

158
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:45,867
And I'm starting to worry

159
00:08:45,933 --> 00:08:47,733
if something bad happened
to her.

160
00:08:49,067 --> 00:08:51,267
Tonito, something happened
to her.

161
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:54,300
Huh?

162
00:09:13,567 --> 00:09:14,733
Here.

163
00:09:14,800 --> 00:09:17,100
Let's eat first
before we go back.

164
00:09:20,133 --> 00:09:21,467
That looks bad.

165
00:09:21,533 --> 00:09:22,400
I won't eat that.

166
00:09:22,467 --> 00:09:24,500
It looks bitter.

167
00:09:24,567 --> 00:09:25,900
You better eat that alone
instead.

168
00:09:25,967 --> 00:09:27,433
That's your buffet.

169
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:29,700
Are you sure?

170
00:09:29,767 --> 00:09:31,100
Yes.

171
00:09:35,633 --> 00:09:36,867
You're hungry.

172
00:09:36,933 --> 00:09:38,533
Come on, lower your pride.

173
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:39,700
You eat.

174
00:09:39,767 --> 00:09:41,333
I don't want to.
I'll eat at home.

175
00:09:44,133 --> 00:09:45,767
Are you sure? I'll give this
to Grandmother Ikay.

176
00:09:46,800 --> 00:09:47,500
Then give it to her.

177
00:09:50,700 --> 00:09:53,033
Okay, I'll put this in the car.

178
00:09:53,100 --> 00:09:54,233
We'll leave in a while.

179
00:10:15,967 --> 00:10:17,800
Tonito, the chopper is ready.

180
00:10:17,867 --> 00:10:20,567
I already told your assistant
to call Madam Vivian

181
00:10:20,633 --> 00:10:22,433
to move the meeting.

182
00:10:22,500 --> 00:10:23,567
Okay, good.

183
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:26,400
What's the problem?

184
00:10:26,467 --> 00:10:27,700
Why did you move our meeting?

185
00:10:28,900 --> 00:10:30,567
Celeste is in trouble.

186
00:10:30,633 --> 00:10:32,000
I need to go to her.

187
00:10:32,067 --> 00:10:34,067
And just for that woman...

188
00:10:34,133 --> 00:10:36,733
you will move this
important meeting with me?

189
00:10:36,833 --> 00:10:39,933
Vivian,
she's not just any woman.

190
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:43,000
She's my fiancé.

191
00:10:43,067 --> 00:10:44,467
I'll talk to you
when I get back.

192
00:10:44,533 --> 00:10:46,333
But I'm sorry I really
have to leave now.

193
00:11:12,967 --> 00:11:13,967
Let's go.

194
00:11:18,800 --> 00:11:20,433
Can you manage? Come.

195
00:11:20,500 --> 00:11:21,333
It's okay. I can manage.

196
00:11:22,433 --> 00:11:23,633
I can manage alone.

197
00:11:28,167 --> 00:11:29,467
Does it still hurt?

198
00:11:29,533 --> 00:11:30,400
Not that much.

199
00:11:30,467 --> 00:11:31,633
It's already manageable.

200
00:11:36,833 --> 00:11:37,733
What? Are you okay?

201
00:11:39,433 --> 00:11:40,800
Nothing. I just feel dizzy.

202
00:11:41,833 --> 00:11:43,233
It's because you didn't eat.

203
00:11:44,333 --> 00:11:45,233
Come on, I'll carry you.

204
00:11:46,700 --> 00:11:48,433
No, I'm okay. I can manage.

205
00:11:49,367 --> 00:11:51,333
Come on, I'll carry you
like what we used to do before.

206
00:11:56,467 --> 00:11:58,033
Mikoy, it looks like
it will rain.

207
00:11:59,667 --> 00:12:00,567
You're right.

208
00:12:01,433 --> 00:12:02,433
Shall we run now?

209
00:12:02,500 --> 00:12:04,467
We might get
caught in the rain.

210
00:12:04,533 --> 00:12:05,733
- Come on, let's go.
- Okay.

211
00:12:08,200 --> 00:12:08,967
Wait, Mikoy.

212
00:12:09,033 --> 00:12:10,167
Ah!

213
00:12:10,233 --> 00:12:11,167
Mikoy!

214
00:12:12,233 --> 00:12:13,633
Celeste, are you okay?

215
00:12:13,700 --> 00:12:14,800
- Mikoy, ah....
- Celeste?

216
00:12:14,900 --> 00:12:16,500
- It hurts.
- Celeste, are you okay?

217
00:12:16,567 --> 00:12:18,367
- Can you stand up?
- I think I'm wounded.

218
00:12:18,433 --> 00:12:19,867
Stand up. Can you do it?

219
00:12:19,933 --> 00:12:20,467
Ah...

220
00:12:21,433 --> 00:12:22,200
Can you manage?

221
00:12:22,267 --> 00:12:23,467
No.

222
00:12:25,367 --> 00:12:26,400
You're wounded?

223
00:12:27,667 --> 00:12:28,667
Come on, I'll carry
you on my back.

224
00:12:33,033 --> 00:12:34,467
Let's go?

225
00:12:34,533 --> 00:12:36,700
Yes.

226
00:12:36,767 --> 00:12:37,633
Are you all right?

227
00:12:37,700 --> 00:12:39,367
It hurts.

228
00:12:45,067 --> 00:12:46,500
What? Come on.

229
00:12:46,567 --> 00:12:48,300
It's up to you.
You're getting married.

230
00:12:48,400 --> 00:12:49,400
And I'm prone
to accidents.

231
00:12:49,467 --> 00:12:50,133
Okay, I'll do it.
Come on.

232
00:12:52,167 --> 00:12:54,200
All right...

233
00:12:54,267 --> 00:12:56,233
Ready. One,
two,three, up!

234
00:12:56,300 --> 00:12:59,300
Ouch! You're heavy!

235
00:13:01,067 --> 00:13:02,400
Let's go?

236
00:13:02,467 --> 00:13:05,900
Okay.

237
00:13:05,967 --> 00:13:07,567
You're heavy.

238
00:13:07,633 --> 00:13:08,867
I'm not eating anymore.

239
00:13:18,667 --> 00:13:22,333
Clau is not feeling well
so James and I will go with you.

240
00:13:24,133 --> 00:13:25,633
Your boyfriend
is no longer a war freak?

241
00:13:28,800 --> 00:13:29,933
Don't worry.
I'll explained to him

242
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:32,333
everything about our scheme...

243
00:13:32,400 --> 00:13:33,500
and he agreed.

244
00:13:34,367 --> 00:13:35,200
I just want to make it clear

245
00:13:35,267 --> 00:13:37,000
because that fool might get mad
again.

246
00:13:38,367 --> 00:13:39,467
Who is a fool?

247
00:13:39,533 --> 00:13:40,033
Oh...

248
00:13:40,133 --> 00:13:41,300
Chill.

249
00:13:41,367 --> 00:13:42,300
Jerk.

250
00:13:42,367 --> 00:13:43,400
Fool.

251
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:45,333
- Jerk.
- Fool.

252
00:13:45,400 --> 00:13:46,033
- Oh my God.
- Fool.

253
00:13:46,100 --> 00:13:48,233
- You know...
- Jerk.

254
00:13:48,300 --> 00:13:50,233
both of you are a jerk
and a fool

255
00:13:50,300 --> 00:13:52,000
if you don't stop.

256
00:13:52,067 --> 00:13:53,067
Sir Ben might hear us.

257
00:13:53,133 --> 00:13:54,433
We are in his house.

258
00:13:55,433 --> 00:13:57,000
Hey, Kids.

259
00:13:57,767 --> 00:13:59,000
Are you all ready?

260
00:13:59,967 --> 00:14:02,000
Yes, let's go!

261
00:14:02,067 --> 00:14:02,900
Come on.

262
00:14:17,067 --> 00:14:19,400
We'll stay at the back, right?

263
00:14:20,067 --> 00:14:22,100
Make yourself comfortable.

264
00:14:22,167 --> 00:14:24,033
Just wait.

265
00:15:18,367 --> 00:15:19,900
Thank you for taking me home,
Mikoy.

266
00:15:21,867 --> 00:15:24,933
That's okay.
And if you need service,

267
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:26,700
wherever you want to go,
it's free of charge.

268
00:15:29,033 --> 00:15:30,367
I'll go ahead.

269
00:15:30,433 --> 00:15:33,500
I just want to say...

270
00:15:33,567 --> 00:15:36,200
thank you for taking care of me.

271
00:15:36,300 --> 00:15:38,700
And being so good to me

272
00:15:38,767 --> 00:15:40,933
even if I'm a bit
of a troublemaker.

273
00:15:42,833 --> 00:15:44,200
It's okay to make mistakes.

274
00:15:45,133 --> 00:15:46,633
What's important
is we learn, right?

275
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:54,567
And besides, I'm happy
when I'm with you...

276
00:15:54,633 --> 00:15:55,933
even if you are a troublemaker.

277
00:16:06,800 --> 00:16:07,933
Celeste?

278
00:16:14,633 --> 00:16:15,867
Celeste?

279
00:16:15,933 --> 00:16:16,933
Tonito?

280
00:17:43,133 --> 00:17:44,433
James...

281
00:17:57,233 --> 00:17:58,600
I'm so worried about you.

282
00:17:58,667 --> 00:18:00,433
We didn't talk the whole day
yesterday.

283
00:18:00,500 --> 00:18:03,333
I know.
Don't worry, I'm fine.

284
00:18:03,400 --> 00:18:06,233
I just didn't expect that
we will get stranded.

285
00:18:06,967 --> 00:18:11,433
By the way, this is Mikoy...

286
00:18:11,500 --> 00:18:12,900
my childhood friend.

287
00:18:13,833 --> 00:18:17,933
He actually took care of me
when I got stranded.

288
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:19,600
I owe my life to him.

289
00:18:19,667 --> 00:18:20,500
If it weren't for him

290
00:18:20,567 --> 00:18:22,833
maybe something bad happened
to me.

291
00:18:24,533 --> 00:18:25,600
Mikoy.

292
00:18:25,667 --> 00:18:27,100
Hi.

293
00:18:27,167 --> 00:18:28,567
Tonito.

294
00:18:29,700 --> 00:18:32,533
I'm so grateful
for your kindness to Celeste.

295
00:18:32,600 --> 00:18:33,700
Thank you so much.

296
00:18:34,533 --> 00:18:38,100
If you need anything
and I can help...

297
00:18:38,167 --> 00:18:39,333
don't hesitate to call me.

298
00:18:46,267 --> 00:18:47,267
Thank you again.

299
00:18:50,233 --> 00:18:51,833
I'll rest.

300
00:18:51,900 --> 00:18:52,967
I'll go ahead.

301
00:18:53,033 --> 00:18:56,400
Celeste, good thing
nothing bad happened to you.

302
00:18:56,500 --> 00:18:58,667
I'm sorry I wasn't able
to tell...

303
00:18:58,733 --> 00:19:00,700
Father, that's okay.

304
00:19:03,067 --> 00:19:05,200
Let's visit mother
some other day.

305
00:19:06,667 --> 00:19:09,500
Celeste, don't worry.

306
00:19:09,567 --> 00:19:11,033
We visit your mother

307
00:19:11,100 --> 00:19:12,600
even if it's not
her death anniversary.

308
00:19:15,833 --> 00:19:17,700
Thank you.

309
00:19:17,767 --> 00:19:18,600
I have to go.

310
00:19:24,133 --> 00:19:26,067
Thank you so much.

311
00:19:26,133 --> 00:19:27,567
Mikoy, why don't you have lunch
here?

312
00:19:27,633 --> 00:19:29,833
Eat with us.

313
00:19:29,933 --> 00:19:31,467
Thank you, Sir.

314
00:19:31,533 --> 00:19:34,500
Grandmother Ikay
is waiting for me.

315
00:19:34,567 --> 00:19:35,700
She is worried about me.

316
00:19:35,767 --> 00:19:37,100
Okay.

317
00:19:37,167 --> 00:19:38,733
Thank you so much again, Mikoy.

318
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:41,267
One of these days,

319
00:19:41,333 --> 00:19:42,567
I'll visit you
and your Grandmother Ikay.

320
00:19:43,467 --> 00:19:45,133
Okay.

321
00:19:45,200 --> 00:19:46,300
I'll tell Grandmother.

322
00:19:47,467 --> 00:19:49,633
- I'll go ahead.
- Thank you so much!

323
00:19:49,700 --> 00:19:51,233
- Bye.
- You take care.

324
00:20:03,733 --> 00:20:05,533
Ready. One, two,
three, up!

325
00:20:05,600 --> 00:20:07,533
Ouch!

326
00:20:07,600 --> 00:20:08,733
You're heavy.

327
00:20:10,367 --> 00:20:11,233
Let's go.

328
00:20:15,233 --> 00:20:17,000
You're heavy.

329
00:20:17,067 --> 00:20:18,633
I'm not eating anymore.

330
00:20:39,700 --> 00:20:42,133
You trying to trick us
with your stories, Tonito.

331
00:20:42,200 --> 00:20:43,700
How many servings of Timitim
have you had?

332
00:20:44,900 --> 00:20:47,333
This is the first time
I tried Timitim.

333
00:20:47,400 --> 00:20:49,000
This is delicious.

334
00:20:49,067 --> 00:20:51,133
You're lucky
we still have that.

335
00:20:51,200 --> 00:20:53,333
They rarely do that
in the forest.

336
00:20:54,600 --> 00:20:56,367
That's Celeste's favorite.

337
00:20:56,433 --> 00:20:58,867
What a pity she's on a diet
right now.

338
00:20:58,933 --> 00:21:00,033
Yes.

339
00:21:00,100 --> 00:21:01,267
Maybe I can suggest to Celeste

340
00:21:01,333 --> 00:21:04,167
to prepare Sorsogon dishes
at our wedding.

341
00:21:05,167 --> 00:21:06,533
That is if she will agree.

342
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:11,467
We will help you find someone

343
00:21:11,567 --> 00:21:18,200
good at cooking Timitim
and Pinangat here in Sorsogon.

344
00:21:18,267 --> 00:21:20,800
And Grandmother Ikay
is one of them.

345
00:21:20,867 --> 00:21:23,467
What are your plans
for the wedding?

346
00:21:24,367 --> 00:21:26,467
Well, no definite
plans yet.

347
00:21:26,533 --> 00:21:28,100
Her return to Manila
was delayed

348
00:21:28,167 --> 00:21:29,700
because of her
community service.

349
00:21:32,133 --> 00:21:35,600
As for us,
whatever your plans are,

350
00:21:35,667 --> 00:21:38,000
we're just here
to support you.

351
00:21:39,367 --> 00:21:40,267
Thank you.

352
00:21:41,500 --> 00:21:42,900
All I want to do is make Celeste

353
00:21:42,967 --> 00:21:44,967
the happiest woman in the world.

354
00:21:46,167 --> 00:21:47,967
I never dreamed of finding
the right woman.

355
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:50,933
And now, I just want
to be the right man

356
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:52,167
for the woman I will love.

357
00:21:52,933 --> 00:21:54,400
You made us happy, Tonito.

358
00:21:55,433 --> 00:21:58,367
We are sure that Celeste
will be happy with you.

359
00:21:58,433 --> 00:22:02,333
And Patricio and I will be happy
also for the both of you.

360
00:22:03,067 --> 00:22:05,733
And we will be happier

361
00:22:05,800 --> 00:22:09,300
if you will give us
a grandchild right away.

362
00:22:11,533 --> 00:22:12,967
Don't worry.

363
00:22:13,033 --> 00:22:15,933
After the wedding,
we'll do overtime for that.

364
00:22:16,033 --> 00:22:17,667
That is my and Celeste's
first project.

365
00:22:23,533 --> 00:22:24,867
Just keep eating.

366
00:22:47,133 --> 00:22:48,100
What are you doing?

367
00:22:48,200 --> 00:22:49,433
Wait.

368
00:22:49,500 --> 00:22:50,733
Just relax there.

369
00:22:54,333 --> 00:22:55,833
That's gross.

370
00:22:55,900 --> 00:22:57,167
You want me not to wear this?

371
00:23:01,900 --> 00:23:03,967
- There.
- What are you doing?

372
00:23:04,033 --> 00:23:05,900
Wait, we'll treat that.

373
00:23:14,367 --> 00:23:17,367
Just a second, let me see.

374
00:23:27,467 --> 00:23:29,300
Oh my God.

375
00:23:29,367 --> 00:23:32,367
Why is it like this?

376
00:23:32,433 --> 00:23:33,867
Why am I thinking of Mikoy?

377
00:23:33,933 --> 00:23:35,500
Can I just erase, erase,
erase this?

378
00:23:37,367 --> 00:23:39,867
I think that fool cast a spell
on me.

379
00:23:44,300 --> 00:23:47,067
I think that fool
cast a spell on me.

380
00:23:53,467 --> 00:23:54,433
Oh my...

381
00:23:55,767 --> 00:23:56,933
What's happening?

382
00:23:58,533 --> 00:24:00,100
I'm so confused.

383
00:24:00,167 --> 00:24:05,100
Why is it like this?
Why am I thinking of Mikoy?

384
00:24:05,167 --> 00:24:07,533
He's coming in my mind.

385
00:24:07,600 --> 00:24:08,633
Why is that?

386
00:24:10,767 --> 00:24:11,800
I'm so confused.

387
00:24:14,467 --> 00:24:15,633
But I love Tonito.

388
00:24:17,767 --> 00:24:19,700
I love Tonito so much.

389
00:24:21,800 --> 00:24:23,433
Tonito brings out
the best in me.

390
00:24:25,533 --> 00:24:26,233
He's so good to me.

391
00:24:26,300 --> 00:24:27,533
He's my biggest blessing...

392
00:24:27,600 --> 00:24:30,400
and we complement each other.

393
00:24:32,300 --> 00:24:33,733
I can't live without him.

394
00:24:37,067 --> 00:24:38,567
Likewise, Love.

395
00:24:38,633 --> 00:24:40,567
I also can't see myself
being without you.

396
00:24:42,867 --> 00:24:43,733
Tonito?

397
00:24:46,767 --> 00:24:47,767
Tonito?

398
00:24:49,633 --> 00:24:51,467
Have you been there that long?

399
00:24:51,533 --> 00:24:53,967
You heard everything I said?

400
00:24:55,500 --> 00:24:57,267
Yes...

401
00:24:57,333 --> 00:24:58,500
why?

402
00:24:58,567 --> 00:25:00,433
Is there anything not true
with what you said about me?

403
00:25:01,500 --> 00:25:03,467
I'm the only Tonito
in your life, right?

404
00:25:22,533 --> 00:25:25,133
Can you guys promise me
that you will behave?

405
00:25:29,467 --> 00:25:31,233
I can't hear a promise.

406
00:25:31,300 --> 00:25:33,467
It's just the two
of you together.

407
00:25:33,533 --> 00:25:35,100
Did nothing happen to you?

408
00:25:35,200 --> 00:25:37,867
Grandmother, she's with the man
she will marry.

409
00:25:37,933 --> 00:25:40,900
It seems like I'm not yet okay
with my father and stepmom.

410
00:25:40,967 --> 00:25:44,467
I find it hard to forgive
them after everything.

411
00:25:44,533 --> 00:25:45,467
You know that we have

412
00:25:45,533 --> 00:25:47,333
the same goal for your dad,
right?

413
00:25:47,400 --> 00:25:50,067
And that is to make our family
whole again.

414
00:25:50,133 --> 00:25:53,767
The only obstacle to our goal
is non other than Celeste.

415
00:25:53,833 --> 00:25:56,033
I want to introduce you
to the person

416
00:25:56,100 --> 00:26:00,067
who I prayed to come
into my life.

417
00:26:00,133 --> 00:26:01,233
Tiff?

418
00:26:01,300 --> 00:26:04,967
Don't call me Tiff.

419
00:26:05,033 --> 00:26:06,967
We're not close.

420
00:26:07,033 --> 00:26:09,867
Even if I marry
your Auntie Celeste,

421
00:26:09,967 --> 00:26:12,200
I will still be your dad.

422
00:26:12,267 --> 00:26:14,000
And your Auntie Celeste
can be your mom.

423
00:26:14,067 --> 00:26:17,567
For me, she's a homewrecker.

424
00:26:17,633 --> 00:26:19,267
Why do you two need
to get married?

425
00:26:19,333 --> 00:26:21,700
Can't you just be with mommy
again?

426
00:26:24,567 --> 00:26:26,333
I guess we have to give her
some more time

427
00:26:26,400 --> 00:26:27,900
to adjust to the situation.

428
00:26:27,967 --> 00:26:29,067
You know what, Love?

429
00:26:29,133 --> 00:26:31,767
It seems like I don't want
to leave yet.

430
00:26:31,833 --> 00:26:33,867
I want to spend more
time here with you.
